 >1) What does LPS mean?  (i.e. LPS Hydrae or Ear LPS)

 Last Planet Stand. If the enemy is down to a few planets, it's useful
 to try to get the hardest ones first (like the home planet) while they
 are still uncertain which planet you're planning to take: i.e. you
 can fake an attack on a different planet in hopes of drawing away
 some defenders. If it gets down to an LPS on the hardest planet, it's
 much harder to take since the enemy knows exactly where you're going.

 >2) What does Rf++ or F1++ or K0++ mean?  The hints docs say it
 >MIGHT mean Rf, F1, and K0 are carrying armies... If that is true
 >how do they know they are carrying armies?  

 If you set your galactic map to show armies ('B') then when you see
 a ship with kills headed to a planet with armies, it's a good bet
 they're picking up...you can get info on the planet before and
 after, count up the difference, and that's how many they carry.

